<item>
            <title>[FLINK-8789] Misleading error message when stopping task that wasn&apos;t started yet</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-8789</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;While porting the &lt;tt&gt;TimestampITCase&lt;/tt&gt; i got a strange exception in the logs when running &lt;tt&gt;testWatermarkPropagationNoFinalWatermarkOnStop&lt;/tt&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
Caused by: java.lang.UnsupportedOperationException: Stopping not supported by task Source: Custom Source (1/1) (87f44b422280be896bdf44766ebeb53e).
&#160;&#160; &#160;at org.apache.flink.runtime.taskmanager.Task.stopExecution(Task.java:965)
&#160;&#160; &#160;at org.apache.flink.runtime.taskexecutor.TaskExecutor.stopTask(TaskExecutor.java:549)
&#160;&#160; &#160;... 18 more&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&#160;This source however implements the &lt;tt&gt;StoppableFunction&lt;/tt&gt; interface.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This happens also against a legacy cluster.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
